READ: UPDATE: Woman killed by elephant in Kruger after attack by herd The situation was monitored and administered by the MTPA under the applicable legislation for such incidents as Matsulu is outside of the park and within the jurisdiction of the agency.
“We received a phone call about three elephant bulls who escaped near Matsulu. Due to the interference of the community, we took a decision to shoot them,” said Lesley Nyawo, spokesman for KNP. The community harvested the meat and other body parts, and it is not clear at this stage whether the ivory was taken.